<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2645641>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Probable dispersal routes for Sphecidae and Crabronidae into the West Indies through alternative scenarios. Stippled arrows show major dispersal corridors for the occupation of the Proto­Antilles, at about 35–33 mya. Percentages are for Cuban species shared with other areas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2645641/files/figure.svg" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2645643>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Map of Cuban areas of highest endemism and biodiversity, and only known localities for some species of apoid wasps." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2645643/files/figure.svg" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

